        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "“Krishi Input Anudan Yojana” launched by the Department of Agriculture, Bihar, is designed to offer agricultural input subsidies in areas affected by rising water levels in rivers such as the Ganga and Kosi. Assistance are provided for crop damage more than 33% caused by heavy rainfall and flooding.\n&lt;br&gt;\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "&gt; **Subsidy Amounts per Hectare:**\n\n\n\n      1. Non-irrigated (year-dependent) crop areas: ₹8,500/-.\n      1. Irrigated crop areas: ₹17,000/-.\n      1. Perpetual/ perennial crops: ₹22,500/-.\n\n\n&gt; **Minimum Subsidy Amounts to Farmers:**\n\n\n\n      1. Non-irrigated (year-dependent) crop areas: ₹1,000/-.\n      1. Irrigated crop areas: ₹2,000/-.\n      1. Perpetual/ perennial crops: ₹2,500/-.\n\n\n",
        "exclusions_md": "<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme aims to provide agricultural input subsidies in affected areas due to the rise in water levels of rivers like Ganga and Kosi and flood-related crop damage from heavy rainfall.\n\n",
